25/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- An international architecture jury selected a proposal Thursday (March 24th) from an Austrian company for a new parliament building in downtown Tirana.
Jury head Johannes Ibelings announced the winner among 12 international projects selected by the jury and voted by the public.
The new buildings will replace the current International Cultural Centre, known as the Pyramid, built during the communist regime.
The pace will be brisk, amid plans is to unveil the building in November 2012, the 100th anniversary of Albania's independence.
(Balkan Web, Top Channel, Shekulli, Ora News - 24/03/11)
